In the late 19th and early 20th century Russian Navy there were literally dozens of foreign sabotage teams freely operating on battleships as part of the crews, German agents, British agents, French spies, others. They would organize mutinies, blow up ammunition, sink ships, etc.

This was done with the full knowledge of treasonous admirals from the upper echelons of the Navy who were masons. With those videos of Chinese language only recruitment offices for the US Navy there are probably already hundreds of agents operating on aircraft carriers and such.

There's that Soviet "Battleship Potemkin" movie about one such mutiny but it was one out of many incidents. It was so bad that at one point the British agents in the Navy actually had to get rid of the German agents there, it completely crippled Russia's military capacity at sea.
